  </a>
  <figcaption id="img-caption"> Dr. Milk was a compassionate doctor by day, and a ruthless businessman by night. </figcaption>

  </div>
  <p id="tribute-info"> 
<b> A timeline of Dr. Milk's life
  </b> 
<ul> 
<li> <time datetime="1950">1950</time> - Born, Sasaki Matahachi Milk, in Hiroshima, Japan </li>  
<li> <time datetime="1960">1960</time> - Moved to Los Angeles, California with his parents and little brother </li>
<li> <time datetime="1968">1968</time> - Enters Harvard University as a Freshman double majoring in Molecular Biology and Physics with a Agriculture minor </li>
 
  <li> <time datetime="1971">1971</time> - Graduated at the top of his class at Harvard University and immediately enters Harvard Medical School </li>
    <li> <time datetime="1983">1983</time> - Dr. Milk's first year as a practicing physician in the state of Texas </li> 
    <li> <time datetime="1990">1985</time> - Falls into a deep depression due to a perceived lack of purpose. Dr. Milk up taking a  professional hiatus to work at a nearby ranch. It was in this ranch that Dr. Milk discovered his true passion. </li>
    <li> <time datetime="1992">1992</time> - He becomes the best milkmaid in the region. He also begins to research influences on the flavor of the milk that the cows produced  </li>
    <li> <time datetime="1993">1993</time> - Dr. Milk buys the ranch to begin his Dairy farming business. He names his company "Big Milk". He also returns to his former profession as a physician to fund his business ventures </li>
    <li> <time datetime="2000">2000</time> - Big Milk reaches the top of the dairy industry. Its success has been attributed to the unique, subtle sweet flavor and the curiously calming effects of a single sip of the milk. </li>
    <li> <time datetime="2005">2005</time> - Dr. Milk is named "The Godfather of Milk". 95% dairy products sold in grocery stores now list Big Milk's formulated milk as a primary ingredient </li>
    <li> <time datetime="2015">2015</time> - Dr. Milk pubicly engages discussion on milk powered technology. Rumors of milk-powered cars begin </li>
    <li> <time datetime="2017">2017</time> - News of the MiLK 5G phone, Milkflix streaming service, and the MilkStation 1 gaming console are leaked to the public. Dr. Milk states "Big Milk will be more than just dairy, soon" </li>
    <li> <time datetime="2018">2018</time> - Dr. Milk dies in Seabrook, Washington. The cause of death was confimred to be from drowning in a vat of milk. Dr. Milk had been testing out his new invention, the Deep Milk Submarine, in a vat about a mile deep and filled with milk. His body was found at the bottom of the vat. Investigators believe that the submarine had ran out of gas, oxygen, and milk started to seep in to the submarine. </li>
    
    </ul>
</p> 
